com21StuPrxy.name: com21StuPrxy
com21StuPrxy.contactinfo: Network Management Postal: Paul Gordon Com21, Inc. 750 Tasman Drive Milpitas, California 95035 USA Tel: +1 408 953 9100 Fax: +1 408 953 9299 E-mail: pgordon@com21.com
com21StuPrxy.description: This is the Com21 ComController ComPort Proxy MIB. COM21 Part# 005-0025-00

stuCtrlMacAddress.name: stuCtrlMacAddress
stuCtrlMacAddress.description: Contains IEEE 802 medium access control address of the ComPort device.

stuUserText.name: stuUserText
stuUserText.description: The ComPort User Text is a non-volatile string which is set by the management system with an arbitrary value. This value does not have to be unique. It's purpose is solely to assist the carrier personnel with identifying the ComPort device.

stuSerialNumber.name: stuSerialNumber
stuSerialNumber.description: The Serial Number is a 10 character serial number used by COM21 to uniquely identify the device.

stuBoardRevision.name: stuBoardRevision
stuBoardRevision.description: This string defines the hardware revision of the ComPort board.

stuUnitRevision.name: stuUnitRevision
stuUnitRevision.description: This string defines the hardware revision of the complete ComPort unit.

stuTunerRevision.name: stuTunerRevision
stuTunerRevision.description: This string defines the hardware revision of the RF Tuner.

stuModelName.name: stuModelName
stuModelName.description: This string defines the ComPort Model Type.

stuUnitManufacturer.name: stuUnitManufacturer
stuUnitManufacturer.description: This string defines the manufacturer of the ComPort. Initially COM21 and 3COM.

stuDesKeySize.name: stuDesKeySize
stuDesKeySize.description: DES encryption key size supported by the ComPort.

stuMibRevision.name: stuMibRevision
stuMibRevision.description: Indicates the Mib Revision as display string of max. 8 bytes. That includes string terminator.

stuRestartAction.name: stuRestartAction
stuRestartAction.description: The Restart Action is an active-value. The setting of this value is idempotent. The setting of this value to restart causes the STU to restart utilizing the present software load.

stuPrevTestResult.name: stuPrevTestResult
stuPrevTestResult.description: Result of previous test. Presently this will be warm or cold restart.

stuPrevTestFailCode.name: stuPrevTestFailCode
stuPrevTestFailCode.description: Failure result code. Only set if stuPrevTestResult is equal to failure.

stuOperationState.name: stuOperationState
stuOperationState.description: The ComPort Operational State is controlled either by the stuAdminState or locally detected conditions. Note that downloading and failedRanging are ComController helded states.

stuAimModuleId.name: stuAimModuleId
stuAimModuleId.description: identifies the connected AIM module type. The maceEthernet entry indicates NO AIM inserted.

stuMaceFail.name: stuMaceFail
stuMaceFail.description: This trap would be sent after ComPort is completely booted. That is, at least download is completed. Event will be detected during POST (Power On Self Test)

stuUpstrmTestFreq.name: stuUpstrmTestFreq
stuUpstrmTestFreq.description: Transmit Frequency used by ComPort for Upstream RF test. The default shall be 0 (an invalid freq).

stuInbPresent.name: stuInbPresent
stuInbPresent.description: Indicates if the INB is present on the ComPORT. This is a future item not supported by present ComPORT hardware.

stuInbContToneEnable.name: stuInbContToneEnable
stuInbContToneEnable.description: Controls the activation of a continuous pilot tone. This does not effect the standard tone sent before data (which is controlled by a hardware switch). This value is not stored in NVRAM. Default is disable.

stuLastRestartCause.name: stuLastRestartCause
stuLastRestartCause.description: specifies the reason for the last ComPort reset.

stuUpstrmPingCntrl.name: stuUpstrmPingCntrl
stuUpstrmPingCntrl.description: used to control the upstream ping. Default is enable.

stuUpstrmTestTimeout.name: stuUpstrmTestTimeout
stuUpstrmTestTimeout.description: timeout used by ComPort for Upstream RF test. If the ComController does not terminate the test in this period - defined in seconds - then the ComPort will automatically reset, thus terminating the test. 0 means no timeout. Default is 0.

stuDnstrmAltFreq.name: stuDnstrmAltFreq
stuDnstrmAltFreq.description: Defines an alternate downstream frequency for the ComPort. This value is non-voltile. Default is 0 (an invalid freq). IMPORTANT - this is a tbd feature not available in 2.3 release.

stuAsicRevision.name: stuAsicRevision
stuAsicRevision.description: defines the revision of the ASIC. Presently values 1-255 are supported.

stuVoiceAimLpBk.name: stuVoiceAimLpBk
stuVoiceAimLpBk.description: If a voiceAim Module is configured on the stu, setting the Aim Module to stuLpBk will configure the Aim Module to loopback from one voice port to the other. default: nil

stuVoiceAimPort1Status.name: stuVoiceAimPort1Status
stuVoiceAimPort1Status.description: Describes whether the AimPort is onhook or offhook. default: nil

stuVoiceAimPort2Status.name: stuVoiceAimPort2Status
stuVoiceAimPort2Status.description: Describes whether the AimPort is onhook or offhook. default: nil

stuPhyMacAddress.name: stuPhyMacAddress
stuPhyMacAddress.description: Contains IEEE 802 medium access control address of the ComPort device.

stuXmitFrequency.name: stuXmitFrequency
stuXmitFrequency.description: Contains the transmit frequency of the ComPort RF board in KHz. A change in this value shall result in the ComPort being hopped to a differing RX card. The Common Controller shall ensure the sanity of a change to this attribute and shall perform the necessary interface to the RX cards. The actual set of this attribute on the ComPort shall be performed by a GO_SET message.

stuXmitFeqChange.name: stuXmitFeqChange
stuXmitFeqChange.description: This trap is generated whenever an ComPort is hopped. It will not be generated at initial acquisition.

stuRecvFrequency.name: stuRecvFrequency
stuRecvFrequency.description: Contains the receive frequency in KHz. This attribute will match the downstream frequency of the ComController. The ONLY time when this should be change is when the NMAPS wishes hop the ComPort to a different ComController.

stuRecvRfSrEstimate.name: stuRecvRfSrEstimate
stuRecvRfSrEstimate.description: Received Signal S/R estimate in dB on Rf Downstream. This value is an approximation in dB. Received value should be divided by 10 to get a fixed point representation. e.g., value 185 means 18.5 dB.

stuRecvRfSigLevel.name: stuRecvRfSigLevel
stuRecvRfSigLevel.description: Received Signal Level in dBmv on Rf Downstream.

stuOutOfSpecRFCond.name: stuOutOfSpecRFCond
stuOutOfSpecRFCond.description: This trap is generated whenever an ComPort is acquired with out of spec signal quality condition. The trap trap is issued after the GO-SET-DONE message.

stuXmitOffset.name: stuXmitOffset
stuXmitOffset.description: Specifies the transmit offset of the ComPort.

stuXmitDacVRef.name: stuXmitDacVRef
stuXmitDacVRef.description: Specifies the upstream RF DAC Voltage Reference. This value is set only via a GO_SET message under the control of the RX card.

stuAlmMacAddress.name: stuAlmMacAddress
stuAlmMacAddress.description: Contains IEEE 802 medium access control address of the ComPort device.

stuAlmTime.name: stuAlmTime
stuAlmTime.description: Specifies the time the alarm condition was detected.

stuAlmSevMacAddress.name: stuAlmSevMacAddress
stuAlmSevMacAddress.description: Contains IEEE 802 medium access control address of the ComPort device.

stuAlmSevCrcThres.name: stuAlmSevCrcThres
stuAlmSevCrcThres.description: Specifies the CRC Error Threshold alarm severity. Default Minor.

stuAlmSevTeiThres.name: stuAlmSevTeiThres
stuAlmSevTeiThres.description: Specifies the TEI Threshold alarm severity. Default Minor.

stuAlmSevHecThres.name: stuAlmSevHecThres
stuAlmSevHecThres.description: Specifies the HEC Error Threshold alarm severity. Default Minor.

stuAlmSevEsThres.name: stuAlmSevEsThres
stuAlmSevEsThres.description: Specifies the Errored Seconds Threshold alarm severity. Default Minor.

stuAlmSevFecThres.name: stuAlmSevFecThres
stuAlmSevFecThres.description: Specifies the Corrected FEC Threshold alarm severity. Default Minor.

stuEthMacAddress.name: stuEthMacAddress
stuEthMacAddress.description: Contains IEEE 802 medium access control address of the ComPort device. Held on ComController.

stuEtherForwArpOnly.name: stuEtherForwArpOnly
stuEtherForwArpOnly.description: If enable state then only ARP broadcast packets are forwarded upstream. Default is disable.

stuEtherMacFiltAge.name: stuEtherMacFiltAge
stuEtherMacFiltAge.description: Specifies the number of seconds that a learned MAC Address entry survives since last learning.

stuEtherBCastRateEn.name: stuEtherBCastRateEn
stuEtherBCastRateEn.description: Enable rate control. Default is disabled.

stuEtherBCastRateCo.name: stuEtherBCastRateCo
stuEtherBCastRateCo.description: Limit of maximum number of broadcast packets per second allowed upstream.

stuEtherStickyBitCtrl.name: stuEtherStickyBitCtrl
stuEtherStickyBitCtrl.description: When the Sticky Bit control is enabled, a MAC table entry will not be replaced by another MAC address for at least one aging period. Default disable.

stuEther8021QEnable.name: stuEther8021QEnable
stuEther8021QEnable.description: Enables both 802.1Q priority queuing and the filter of 802.1Q format packets. Default disable.

stuEtherNonSnapRej.name: stuEtherNonSnapRej
stuEtherNonSnapRej.description: This attribute controls the filtering of 802.2 non- SNAP encoded packets. Ethernet type filtering must be enabled to activate this feature. Default disable.

stuEtherIgmpEnable.name: stuEtherIgmpEnable
stuEtherIgmpEnable.description: This attribute controls the forwarding of IGMP multicast traffic upstream. This attribute will override any other multicast filtering in the case of IGMP packets. Default is enable.

stuEtherNonIpMultiEn.name: stuEtherNonIpMultiEn
stuEtherNonIpMultiEn.description: This attribute controls the forwarding of non-IP multicast traffic upstream. This attribute will override any other multicast filtering in the case of non-IP multicast packets. Default is enable.

stuEtherBcmpOnly.name: stuEtherBcmpOnly
stuEtherBcmpOnly.description: When this attribute is enabled, all non-BCMP traffic will be rejected in both the upstream and downstream. This attribute is utilized in a Spannong Tree implementation. Default is disable.

stuEtherIgmpSnoopEnable.name: stuEtherIgmpSnoopEnable
stuEtherIgmpSnoopEnable.description: This attribute controls the snooping of IGMP multicast traffic upstream. Default is disable.

com21StuFiltEthTypeEntry.name: com21StuFiltEthTypeEntry
com21StuFiltEthTypeEntry.description: Holds Ethernet Types codes that are to be passed upstream. Maximum of 6 entries.

stuFiltEtherMacAddr.name: stuFiltEtherMacAddr
stuFiltEtherMacAddr.description: Contains IEEE 802 medium access control address of the ComPort device. Held on ComController.

stuFiltEtherType.name: stuFiltEtherType
stuFiltEtherType.description: Holds Ethernet Type codes that is to be passed upstream. Held on ComPort.

stuFiltEtherStatus.name: stuFiltEtherStatus
stuFiltEtherStatus.description: This attribute is used to create or delete Ethernet Type entry.

com21StuFiltIpMultiEntry.name: com21StuFiltIpMultiEntry
com21StuFiltIpMultiEntry.description: Holds IP Multicast Addresses that are to be allowed in either upstream, or downstream, or both directions. Maximum of 16 entries.

stuFiltIpMacAddr.name: stuFiltIpMacAddr
stuFiltIpMacAddr.description: Contains IEEE 802 medium access control address of the ComPort device. Held on ComController.

stuFiltIpMultiAddr.name: stuFiltIpMultiAddr
stuFiltIpMultiAddr.description: Holds Multicast Address. Held on ComPort. Valid values are within the range of MAC addresses of 01.00.5E.00.00.00 to 01.00.5E.7F.FF.FF

stuFiltIpMultiStatus.name: stuFiltIpMultiStatus
stuFiltIpMultiStatus.description: Used to delete or create an entry.

stuFiltIpDirectCntrl.name: stuFiltIpDirectCntrl
stuFiltIpDirectCntrl.description: Used to control the filter direction. Default is bothDirections.

com21StuEtherMacEntry.name: com21StuEtherMacEntry
com21StuEtherMacEntry.description: Holds Ethernet MAC address that are to be processed as specified. Maximum of 8 entries.

stuEtherStuMac.name: stuEtherStuMac
stuEtherStuMac.description: Contains IEEE 802 medium access control address of the ComPort device. Held on ComController.

stuEtherMacAddr.name: stuEtherMacAddr
stuEtherMacAddr.description: Holds MAC address. Held on ComPort.

stuEtherMacType.name: stuEtherMacType
stuEtherMacType.description: Holds action to be performed upon packets of the specified MAC address. In the case of the learned MAC address, this entry becomes read only. Held on ComPort.

stuEtherMacStatus.name: stuEtherMacStatus
stuEtherMacStatus.description: Used to create or delete an entry.

stuEthStatsMacAddr.name: stuEthStatsMacAddr
stuEthStatsMacAddr.description: Contains IEEE 802 medium access control address of the ComPort device. Held on ComController.

stuCurrEtherRunts.name: stuCurrEtherRunts
stuCurrEtherRunts.description: Contains number of runt packets received by the ComPort in the current 15minute period. This data is held on the ComPort.

stuCurrEtherCollitns.name: stuCurrEtherCollitns
stuCurrEtherCollitns.description: Contains number of collisions detected by the ComPort in the current 15minute period. This data is held on the ComPort.

stuCurrEtherFramErrs.name: stuCurrEtherFramErrs
stuCurrEtherFramErrs.description: Contains number of Ethernet Packets with Framing Errors detected by the ComPort in the current 15minute period. This data is held on the ComPort.

stuCurrEtherCrcErrs.name: stuCurrEtherCrcErrs
stuCurrEtherCrcErrs.description: Contains number of Ethernet Packets with CRC Errors detected by the ComPort in the current 15minute period. This data is held on the ComPort.

stuCurrEtherCrcThres.name: stuCurrEtherCrcThres
stuCurrEtherCrcThres.description: contains 15minute error level at which a threshold trap shall be generated. This is mapped to theComPort alarm severity entry stuThresholdLevel. Default is 0 - threshold disabled.

stuCurrEtherTxUnder.name: stuCurrEtherTxUnder
stuCurrEtherTxUnder.description: Contains number of times Ethernet TX FIFO Underflow occurred on transmit queue in the current 15minute period.

stuCurrEtherRxOver.name: stuCurrEtherRxOver
stuCurrEtherRxOver.description: Contains number of times Ethernet RX FIFO Overflow occurred on a receive queue in the current 15minute period.

stuCurrEtherDropFrms.name: stuCurrEtherDropFrms
stuCurrEtherDropFrms.description: Contains number of receive frames dropped by MACE controller in the current 15minute period.

stuPrevEtherRunts.name: stuPrevEtherRunts
stuPrevEtherRunts.description: Contains number of runt packets received by the ComPort in the previous 15minute period. This data is held on the ComPort.

stuPrevEtherCollitns.name: stuPrevEtherCollitns
stuPrevEtherCollitns.description: Contains number of collisions detected by the ComPort in the previous 15minute period. This data is held on the ComPort.

stuPrevEtherFramErrs.name: stuPrevEtherFramErrs
stuPrevEtherFramErrs.description: Contains number of Ethernet Packets with Framing Errors detected by the ComPort in the previous 15minute period. This data is held on the ComPort.

stuPrevEtherCrcErrs.name: stuPrevEtherCrcErrs
stuPrevEtherCrcErrs.description: Contains number of Ethernet Packets with CRC Errors detected by the ComPort in the previous 15minute period. This data is held on the ComPort.

stuPrevEtherTxUnder.name: stuPrevEtherTxUnder
stuPrevEtherTxUnder.description: Contains number of times Ethernet TX FIFO Underflow occurred on transmit queue in the previous 15minute period.

stuPrevEtherRxOver.name: stuPrevEtherRxOver
stuPrevEtherRxOver.description: Contains number of times Ethernet RX FIFO Overflow occurred on a receive queue in the previous 15minute period.

stuPrevEtherDropFrms.name: stuPrevEtherDropFrms
stuPrevEtherDropFrms.description: Contains number of receive frames dropped by MACE controller in the previous 15minute period.

stuEtherClearStats.name: stuEtherClearStats
stuEtherClearStats.description: This attribute is used to clear all Ethernet statistics counters in this group. This operation is only possible if the hcxStatsControl attribute is set to wrapCurr.

stuStatsMacAddress.name: stuStatsMacAddress
stuStatsMacAddress.description: Contains IEEE 802 medium access control address of the ComPort device. Held on ComController.

stuStatsCurrAtmTei.name: stuStatsCurrAtmTei
stuStatsCurrAtmTei.description: Number of cells received with transport errors - uncorrectable FEC or HEC errors - in the current 15minute period.

stuAtmTeiThreshold.name: stuAtmTeiThreshold
stuAtmTeiThreshold.description: contains 15minute transport error level at which a threshold trap shall be generated. Default is 0 - threshold disabled.

stuStatsCurrAtmHec.name: stuStatsCurrAtmHec
stuStatsCurrAtmHec.description: Number of cells received with HEC or Encryption errors in the current 15minute period.

stuAtmHecThreshold.name: stuAtmHecThreshold
stuAtmHecThreshold.description: contains 15minute HEC error level at which a threshold trap shall be generated. Default is 0 - threshold disabled.

stuStatsCurrESMin.name: stuStatsCurrESMin
stuStatsCurrESMin.description: Represents the number of errored seconds in the current 15 minute period.

stuESMinThreshold.name: stuESMinThreshold
stuESMinThreshold.description: contains 15minute errored seconds level at which a threshold trap shall be generated. Default is 0 - threshold disabled.

stuStatsCurrFecCorrect.name: stuStatsCurrFecCorrect
stuStatsCurrFecCorrect.description: Fecs corrected by Demodulator on Downstream in the current 15 minute period.

stuFecCorrectThreshold.name: stuFecCorrectThreshold
stuFecCorrectThreshold.description: contains 15minute Fecs corrected level at which a threshold trap shall be generated. Default is 0 - threshold disabled.

stuStatsCurrUASMin.name: stuStatsCurrUASMin
stuStatsCurrUASMin.description: Represents the number of unavailable seconds in the current 15 minute period.

stuStatsPrevAtmTei.name: stuStatsPrevAtmTei
stuStatsPrevAtmTei.description: Number of cells received with transport errors - HEC or uncorrectable FEC errors - in the previous 15minute period.

stuStatsPrevAtmHec.name: stuStatsPrevAtmHec
stuStatsPrevAtmHec.description: Number of cells received with HEC or Encryption errors in the previous 15minute period.

stuStatsPrevESMin.name: stuStatsPrevESMin
stuStatsPrevESMin.description: Represents the number of errored seconds in the previous 15 minute period.

stuStatsPrevFecCorrect.name: stuStatsPrevFecCorrect
stuStatsPrevFecCorrect.description: Fecs corrected by Demodulator on Downstream in the previous 15 minute period.

stuStatsPrevUASMin.name: stuStatsPrevUASMin
stuStatsPrevUASMin.description: Represents the number of unavailable seconds in the previous 15 minute period.

stuStatsClearStats.name: stuStatsClearStats
stuStatsClearStats.description: This attribute is used to clear the all ComPort statistics counters in this group. This operation is only possible if the hcxStatsControl attribute is set to wrapCurr.

stuAtmStuMacAddr.name: stuAtmStuMacAddr
stuAtmStuMacAddr.description: Contains IEEE 802 medium access control address of the ComPort device. Held on ComController.

stuAtmStuQNo.name: stuAtmStuQNo
stuAtmStuQNo.description: This index consists of a number representing a Mongoose queue. For initial phase this number shall equal the associated VCI number. i.e. Ethernet or Telephony VCIs. This VCI number shall be mapped to a Mongoose queue id by the ComController. For 3.0 there is only a single Ethernet queue - queue 5.

stuAtmStatsCurrMinRx.name: stuAtmStatsCurrMinRx
stuAtmStatsCurrMinRx.description: Represents the number of cells or frames successfully received in the current 15 minute period.

stuAtmStatsCurrMinRxDropped.name: stuAtmStatsCurrMinRxDropped
stuAtmStatsCurrMinRxDropped.description: Represents the number of cells or frames dropped in the current 15 minute period.

stuAtmStatsCurrMinCRCErrors.name: stuAtmStatsCurrMinCRCErrors
stuAtmStatsCurrMinCRCErrors.description: Represents the number of cells or frames received with CRC errors in the current 15 minute period.

stuAtmStatsPrevMinRx.name: stuAtmStatsPrevMinRx
stuAtmStatsPrevMinRx.description: Represents the number of cells or frames successfully received in the previous 15 minute period.

stuAtmStatsPrevMinRxDropped.name: stuAtmStatsPrevMinRxDropped
stuAtmStatsPrevMinRxDropped.description: Represents the number of cells or frames dropped in the previous 15 minute period.

stuAtmStatsPrevMinCRCErrors.name: stuAtmStatsPrevMinCRCErrors
stuAtmStatsPrevMinCRCErrors.description: Represents the number of cells or frames received with CRC errors in the previous 15 minute period.

stuAtmStatsClearStats.name: stuAtmStatsClearStats
stuAtmStatsClearStats.description: This attribute is used to clear the ComPort queue statistics counters in this group. This operation is only possible if the hcxStatsControl attribute is set to wrapCurr.

stuCodeStuMacAddr.name: stuCodeStuMacAddr
stuCodeStuMacAddr.description: Contains IEEE 802 medium access control address of the ComPort device. Held on ComController.

stuCodeImageIndex.name: stuCodeImageIndex
stuCodeImageIndex.description: Index to receive information about various images; VxWorks - operating system. ApplicationStu - Image comprising Stu Application, DownloadImage - Image downloaded into DRAM.

stuCodeImageType.name: stuCodeImageType
stuCodeImageType.description: Code image identifier. vxWorks - boot code and OS, boot memory resident, stuBoot - backup application image, boot memory resident, stuNewapp - primary application image, app memory resident, stuDnld - downloaded application supplement (optional), updateApp - downloaded flash update, updates app flash, updateBoth - downloaded flash update, updates boot+app flash.

stuCodeImageVersion.name: stuCodeImageVersion
stuCodeImageVersion.description: Version Description for the Code Image.

stuCodeImageBuildDir.name: stuCodeImageBuildDir
stuCodeImageBuildDir.description: Directory name where image was built.

stuCodeImageDate.name: stuCodeImageDate
stuCodeImageDate.description: Date when the image is built.

stuCodeImageTime.name: stuCodeImageTime
stuCodeImageTime.description: Time when the image is built.

stuVoiceChanStatsMacAddr.name: stuVoiceChanStatsMacAddr
stuVoiceChanStatsMacAddr.description: Contains IEEE 802 medium access control address of the ComPort device.

stuVoiceChanStatsNum.name: stuVoiceChanStatsNum
stuVoiceChanStatsNum.description: Defines the voice port on the Comport device used for Voice.

stuVoiceChanStatsCurrLostCellCnt.name: stuVoiceChanStatsCurrLostCellCnt
stuVoiceChanStatsCurrLostCellCnt.description: Defines the number of times the Comport's voice port received Cells out of sequence in the current 15-min period.

stuVoiceChanStatsCurrDrpdCellCnt.name: stuVoiceChanStatsCurrDrpdCellCnt
stuVoiceChanStatsCurrDrpdCellCnt.description: Defines the number of times the Comport's voice port dropped cells due to Queue Full in the current 15-min period.

stuVoiceChanStatsCurrCrc3ErrCnt.name: stuVoiceChanStatsCurrCrc3ErrCnt
stuVoiceChanStatsCurrCrc3ErrCnt.description: Defines the number of cells Comport's voice port received with CRC3 Errors in the current 15-min period.

stuVoiceChanStatsCurrSetUpFailCnt.name: stuVoiceChanStatsCurrSetUpFailCnt
stuVoiceChanStatsCurrSetUpFailCnt.description: Defines the number of times the Comport's voice port had to drop the calls due to Call Setup Failure in the current 15-min period.

stuVoiceChanStatsCurrTxVoiceCellCnt.name: stuVoiceChanStatsCurrTxVoiceCellCnt
stuVoiceChanStatsCurrTxVoiceCellCnt.description: Defines the number of Voice cells Comport's voice port Queued to Transmit in the current 15-min period.

stuVoiceChanStatsCurrRxVoiceCellCnt.name: stuVoiceChanStatsCurrRxVoiceCellCnt
stuVoiceChanStatsCurrRxVoiceCellCnt.description: Defines the number of Voice cells the Comport's voice port received in the current 15-min period.

stuVoiceChanStatsCurrTxOamCellCnt.name: stuVoiceChanStatsCurrTxOamCellCnt
stuVoiceChanStatsCurrTxOamCellCnt.description: Defines the number of OAM cells Comport's voice port Queued to Transmit in the current 15-min period.

stuVoiceChanStatsCurrRxOamCellCnt.name: stuVoiceChanStatsCurrRxOamCellCnt
stuVoiceChanStatsCurrRxOamCellCnt.description: Defines the number of OAM cells the Comport's voice port received in the current 15-min period.

stuVoiceChanStatsPrevLostCellCnt.name: stuVoiceChanStatsPrevLostCellCnt
stuVoiceChanStatsPrevLostCellCnt.description: Defines the number of times the Comport's voice port received Cells out of sequence in the previous 15-min period.

stuVoiceChanStatsPrevDrpdCellCnt.name: stuVoiceChanStatsPrevDrpdCellCnt
stuVoiceChanStatsPrevDrpdCellCnt.description: Defines the number of times the Comport's voice port dropped cells due to Queue Full in the previous 15-min period.

stuVoiceChanStatsPrevCrc3ErrCnt.name: stuVoiceChanStatsPrevCrc3ErrCnt
stuVoiceChanStatsPrevCrc3ErrCnt.description: Defines the number of cells Comport's voice port received with CRC3 Errors in the previous 15-min period.

stuVoiceChanStatsPrevSetUpFailCnt.name: stuVoiceChanStatsPrevSetUpFailCnt
stuVoiceChanStatsPrevSetUpFailCnt.description: Defines the number of times the Comport's voice port had to drop the calls due to Call Setup Failure in the previous 15-min period.

stuVoiceChanStatsPrevTxVoiceCellCnt.name: stuVoiceChanStatsPrevTxVoiceCellCnt
stuVoiceChanStatsPrevTxVoiceCellCnt.description: Defines the number of Voice cells Comport's voice port Tranmitted in the previous 15-min period

stuVoiceChanStatsPrevRxVoiceCellCnt.name: stuVoiceChanStatsPrevRxVoiceCellCnt
stuVoiceChanStatsPrevRxVoiceCellCnt.description: Defines the number of times the Comport's voice port received Cells out of sequence in the previous 15-min period.

stuVoiceChanStatsPrevTxOamCellCnt.name: stuVoiceChanStatsPrevTxOamCellCnt
stuVoiceChanStatsPrevTxOamCellCnt.description: Defines the number of times the Comport's voice port received Cells out of sequence in the previous 15-min period.

stuVoiceChanStatsPrevRxOamCellCnt.name: stuVoiceChanStatsPrevRxOamCellCnt
stuVoiceChanStatsPrevRxOamCellCnt.description: Defines the number of times the Comport's voice port received Cells out of sequence in the previous 15-min period.

stuVoiceChanStatsClear.name: stuVoiceChanStatsClear
stuVoiceChanStatsClear.description: Provides the capability to clear the statistics. Clearing of statistics allowed only if hcxStatsControl attribute is set to wrapCurr.
